<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="435" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1435,1969,2030]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,1648,2033]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="435" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1969,1994]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Description.</emphasis>
Body length (including forewing): 
<specimenCount box="[703,724,1970,1993]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
5.2 mm. Male coloration (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1162,1969,1994]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[188,1371,201,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1386,195,1896]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Afronirvana africana, ♂: 17. Habitus, dorsal view; 18. Habitus, lateral view; 19. Face; 20. Pygofer side, lateral view; 21. Genital capsule, lateral view; 22. Base of abdomen, ventral view; 23. connective and style, ventral view; 24. Aedeagus, ventral view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/291364/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Figs 17–19</figureCitation>
) predominantly orangeyellow, with a broad longitudinal marginally serrate black band extended from apex of crown to end of forewing, forewing also with apical black markings, upper margin of face with a roundish median black spot. Upper part of frontoclypeus strongly tumid with a sharp median keel (
<figureCitation box="[778,905,1684,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[188,1371,201,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1386,195,1896]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Afronirvana africana, ♂: 17. Habitus, dorsal view; 18. Habitus, lateral view; 19. Face; 20. Pygofer side, lateral view; 21. Genital capsule, lateral view; 22. Base of abdomen, ventral view; 23. connective and style, ventral view; 24. Aedeagus, ventral view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/291364/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Figs 18, 19</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/291321/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" targetBox="[188,1362,205,1880]" targetPageId="3">
